node.text:
Last week @felipenunesskate received his “signature” legs (for “chilling with friends without getting strange looks”) and then we surprised him with his signature skateboard model the next day. Thanks to @mcop_prosthetics @dupedupe & @davisonbob for helping to create all this magic. Felipe’s groundbreaking video will be out soon at @thrashermag but his pro model is available now at @birdhouseskateboards. The more I get to know him, the more impressed I am with his approach to life and unbreakable determination. No excuses!
🎶: @mrcamcole - “Albion”

node.text:
I got a request from PRK to be a guest singer in their online series, as they inch closer to playing live shows again. Most of their default song selections had been done by the time I was able to participate, but one song stood out: In The City. It was the first song I heard from The Jam, and has always been one of my favorites. Here’s my attempt to channel the prolific @paulwellerhq (who just released a new album!). The ending is my version of a mic/tail drop. Enjoy! 
Thanks @darrinpfeiffer @slee9383 @randybradbury @greghetson @alan_d9000 @900films for doing the heavy lifting on this one.

node.text:
After posting our 1999 doubles run last week, the feedback was incredible. I saw thousands of comments about remembering the event, and a genuine love for that era of skating. The nostalgia was so strong that we decided to do it again yesterday (22 years later). Some of the line was embellished - my 720’s are far less consistent than Andy’s these days - but we tried to match the tricks and the camera angles as best we could. And it just wouldn’t have been complete without the legendary @selema calling the action. Thanks for all of your support through these [many, many] years. We love you, and we still love skating as much as ever.
🎥: @cameronsanchez1 & @katnoaga 
Unrelated (but while you’re here): my NFT is finally dropping in 4/26 via @ethernitychain

node.text:
A video I made for our @birdhouseskateboards booth at ASR trade show in 1996 featuring @andrewreynolds @willysantos @paulzitzer @samiharithi, Matt Beach and my limited Lightwave skills. Stoked on this vert footage at @spottampa; it came at a time when very few cared, but I love that we were still trying as hard as ever to push the limits.
🎶: George Baker Selection

node.text:
A typical Bones Brigade demo in 1989, as documented by @gunarsphoto. This was at the Bike Barn in Whitman, MA but it could have been any of the 30+ stops we did on the east coast over a grueling (but fun) 5 weeks that summer. We would set up the obstacles in different configurations each time; like a perilous game of Mousetrap for the sake of variety and sketchy lipslides. And apparently I gave aggressive high-fives in celebration of surviving another performance.
This was one of my favorite tours because I had the privilege of traveling the world with my dearly departed friend Ray Underhill. The memories we created were among the most vivid & impactful of my career. Special thanks to @saiz5412 @tsherms & @ericsanderson1 for the hard work and constant entertainment during these salad days.

node.text: I had the privilege of being guest #2 of the @mademanpodcast with crypto legend and @mademan founder @gonzogardner. We talked about getting bullied, perseverance, Olympics, the perception of “selling-out” and authenticity. Link in bio.

node.text:
Congratulations to @yutohorigome on winning the inaugural Olympic skateboarding event yesterday with this feat of excellence. The Japanese skate scene has been relatively underground for the last 30+ years but I believe this will give it a boost in popularity or at least be a catalyst for more skateparks in the country (and across the world). Looking forward to watching the women’s street event this morning. 
The proper (OG) name for this trick is a “Heli-pop noseslide” btw. You’re welcome.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tony Hawk in Tokyo, Japan with @atibaphoto. May be an image of one or more people and outdoors.
